Python has 3 built in method to sort 
1. sort() 
    . It is a built in method
    . In place sorting

2. sorted()
    . works for any iterable containers
    . Does not modify the passed container return a new list of sorted items
    . Parameters like key and reverse all work in similar way
    . you will get list as a return value

==>Both of them use TimSort and both are stable